<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id121e295c-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s517"><num value="517">§ 517.</num><heading> Purchase of paper in open market</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Joint Committee on Printing may authorize the Director of the Government Publishing Office to purchase paper in open market when they consider the quantity required so small or the want so immediate as not to justify advertisement for proposals.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id121e295d-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1245">82 Stat. 1245</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/235/dH/tI/s1301/c/1">Pub. L. 113–235, div. H, title I, § 1301(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-16">Dec. 16, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2537">128 Stat. 2537</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id121e295e-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id121e295f-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 13 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s11">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 11</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/602">28 Stat. 602</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1917-03-03/ch163/s6">Mar. 3, 1917, ch. 163, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/39/1121">39 Stat. 1121</ref>).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id121e2960-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id121e2961-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2014—<ref href="/us/pl/113/235">Pub. L. 113–235</ref> substituted “Director of the Government Publishing Office” for “Public Printer”.</p>
</note>
